category: FROM THE ITALIAN
category comment: 

clue: Italian for "unknown", it's how you travel when you don't want to be recognized

response: incognito

clue: Tossed at New Year's, it has a name meaning "sweetmeats", the little candies tossed during carnival

response: confetti

clue: These quick appearances by guest stars in films can carve out a little comic "relief"

response: a cameo

clue: Ben Jonson's 1598 comedy "Every Man in His Humour" uses this Italian term for a brothel

response: a bordello

clue: Somewhere along the line this instrument's name lost its big finish of "forte"

response: piano

